# Host variables and credentials are NOT stored in config.env.
# They are provisioned in GCP Secret Manager and synced into the
# `agentgateway-secrets` Kubernetes Secret by the CSI SecretProviderClass
# (see overlays/<env>/secretproviderclass/agentgateway-secrets.yaml), then
# consumed at runtime via godotenv (CSI mount at /etc/secrets/.env).
#
# One GCP secret per key. Naming convention:
#   dev:  projects/neuraltrust-app-dev/secrets/agentgateway-<key>
#   prod: projects/neuraltrust-app-prod/secrets/agentgateway-<key>
#
# Required GCP secrets (value shown is an example of the secret's content):
#
#   agentgateway-db-host             -> 10.0.0.1
#   agentgateway-redis-host          -> 10.0.0.2
#   agentgateway-db-password         -> your-db-password
#   agentgateway-redis-password      -> your-redis-password
#   agentgateway-server-secret-key   -> your-admin-jwt-signing-key
#   agentgateway-sts-signing-key     -> RSA private key PEM (see below)
#   agentgateway-trustguard-client-secret -> TrustGuard client-credentials secret
#   agentgateway-config-sync-token   -> shared bearer token for the snapshot endpoint
#   agentgateway-config-sync-lkg-key -> base64 32-byte (AES-256) key for the LKG cache
#
# These map to the following environment variables inside the containers:
#   DB_HOST, REDIS_HOST, DB_PASSWORD, REDIS_PASSWORD, SERVER_SECRET_KEY, STS_SIGNING_KEY,
#   TRUSTGUARD_CLIENT_SECRET, CONFIG_SYNC_TOKEN, CONFIG_SYNC_LKG_KEY
# DB_NAME and DB_USER default to agentgateway (see overlays/*/config.env).
# TRUSTGUARD_BASE_URL and TRUSTGUARD_CLIENT_ID are non-secret (set in config.env).
#
# DB-less config sync secrets (shared by admin + proxy + mcp via the CSI .env blob):
#   CONFIG_SYNC_TOKEN   - the admin control plane requires it to serve the snapshot
#                         endpoint; proxy/mcp data planes send it to authenticate pulls.
#                         Generate with e.g. `openssl rand -hex 32`.
#   CONFIG_SYNC_LKG_KEY - AES-256 key that encrypts the on-disk last-known-good
#                         snapshot on the data planes. Must be base64 that decodes to
#                         exactly 32 bytes, e.g. `openssl rand -base64 32`.
#
# DB-less config-sync gRPC TLS (prod only — the channel carries registry credentials,
# so it must not be plaintext in a deployed environment). These are PEM files, mounted
# as separate CSI files under /etc/secrets/config-sync/ (see overlays/prod/
# secretproviderclass and patches/config-sync-tls-patch.yaml), NOT part of the .env blob:
#   agentgateway-config-sync-tls-cert -> server certificate (admin listener). Its SAN
#                         MUST include agentgateway-admin.agentgateway.svc.cluster.local.
#   agentgateway-config-sync-tls-key  -> server private key (admin listener).
#   agentgateway-config-sync-tls-ca   -> CA that signed the server cert; the proxy/mcp
#                         data planes verify the server against it.
#
# STS_SIGNING_KEY is REQUIRED for the MCP server when APP_ENV=prod: it signs the
# downstream session/STS tokens (RS256) and backs /.well-known/jwks.json. It must
# be a stable RSA private key so all replicas share the same key. An ephemeral key
# is only generated (and only allowed) outside prod. STS_ISSUER is non-secret and
# defaults to "trustgate"; override it in overlays/*/config.env if needed.
#
# Generate and store the key (one-time, per environment):
#   openssl genrsa 2048 > sts_signing_key.pem
#   # Add it to the agentgateway .env blob in GCP Secret Manager as a new version,
#   # with newlines escaped so godotenv parses a single line, e.g.:
#   #   STS_SIGNING_KEY=-----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\n...\n-----END RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\n
#   # (the signer also accepts a base64-encoded PEM). Then restart the MCP pods.
